*****************Network of electrically coupled Cerebellar Golgi cells.**********************
-Golgi cell model from Solinas et al., Frontiers in Neuroscience. Cell Mechanisms (except synapses and gapjs) are transferred unchanged onto a reconstructed GoC from our lab. Note: soma diameter as in Solinas et al.
-Golgi cell density data from Zoltan Nusser (4600 GoCs/ mm3, rat). Thus in a region of 350x350x80 ->45 cells -Coupling probability and coupling strength from our experimental data.
-Basolateral dendrites have "MultiDecaySyn" synapses (= mossy fiber synapses) -Apical dendrites have "ApicalSyn" synapses (= parallel fiber synapses)
-The gap junctions are: for serial computing: "GapJunc", for parallel computing: "GapJuncCML"
-Background synaptic noise: pf synapses: 0.5 Hz (100 segments), mf synapses: 2 Hz (20 segments)
-Initial Vm from -55 to -65 mV (random distribution).
Note: -Extra hoc code to adjust ENa and EK -Extra hoc code to introduce a variable extra leak conductance at the soma of every cell (to introduce an additional heterogeneity among cells).

objref random_conductance_generator
random_conductance_generator = new Random()
random_conductance_generator.MCellRan4()
This is the default configuration of the Cell Groups, stimulations, plots, etc for this project
